HEADWORD: Hosta
<hw>Hosta</hw> <pos>prop. n.</pos> <def>A genus of robust East Asian
clump-forming perennial herbs having racemose flowers: plantain lilies;
sometimes placed in the family <fam>Hostaceae</fam>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> genus <gen>Hosta</gen>, Funka, genus
<gen>Funka</gen>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

